30/*
31 * This header file defines the userspace API to the wireless stack. Please
32 * be careful not to break things - i.e. don't move anything around or so
33 * unless you can demonstrate that it breaks neither API nor ABI.
34 *
35 * Additions to the API should be accompanied by actual implementations in
36 * an upstream driver, so that example implementations exist in case there
37 * are ever concerns about the precise semantics of the API or changes are
38 * needed, and to ensure that code for dead (no longer implemented) API
39 * can actually be identified and removed.
40 * Nonetheless, semantics should also be documented carefully in this file.
41 */
42

6097/*
6098 * enum nl80211_ftm_responder_stats - FTM responder statistics
6099 *
6100 * These attribute types are used with %NL80211_ATTR_FTM_RESPONDER_STATS
6101 * when getting FTM responder statistics.
6102 *
6103 * @__NL80211_FTM_STATS_INVALID: attribute number 0 is reserved
6104 * @NL80211_FTM_STATS_SUCCESS_NUM: number of FTM sessions in which all frames
6105 * were ssfully answered (u32)
6106 * @NL80211_FTM_STATS_PARTIAL_NUM: number of FTM sessions in which part of the
6107 * frames were successfully answered (u32)
6108 * @NL80211_FTM_STATS_FAILED_NUM: number of failed FTM sessions (u32)
6109 * @NL80211_FTM_STATS_ASAP_NUM: number of ASAP sessions (u32)
6110 * @NL80211_FTM_STATS_NON_ASAP_NUM: number of non-ASAP sessions (u32)
6111 * @NL80211_FTM_STATS_TOTAL_DURATION_MSEC: total sessions durations - gives an
6112 * indication of how much time the responder was busy (u64, msec)
6113 * @NL80211_FTM_STATS_UNKNOWN_TRIGGERS_NUM: number of unknown FTM triggers -
6114 * triggers from initiators that didn't finish successfully the negotiation
6115 * phase with the responder (u32)
6116 * @NL80211_FTM_STATS_RESCHEDULE_REQUESTS_NUM: number of FTM reschedule requests
6117 * - initiator asks for a new scheduling although it already has scheduled
6118 * FTM slot (u32)
6119 * @NL80211_FTM_STATS_OUT_OF_WINDOW_TRIGGERS_NUM: number of FTM triggers out of
6120 * scheduled window (u32)
6121 * @NL80211_FTM_STATS_PAD: used for padding, ignore
6122 * @__NL80211_TXQ_ATTR_AFTER_LAST: Internal
6123 * @NL80211_FTM_STATS_MAX: highest possible FTM responder stats attribute
6124 */
6125enum nl80211_ftm_responder_stats {
6126 __NL80211_FTM_STATS_INVALID,
6127 NL80211_FTM_STATS_SUCCESS_NUM,
6128 NL80211_FTM_STATS_PARTIAL_NUM,
6129 NL80211_FTM_STATS_FAILED_NUM,
6130 NL80211_FTM_STATS_ASAP_NUM,
6131 NL80211_FTM_STATS_NON_ASAP_NUM,
6132 NL80211_FTM_STATS_TOTAL_DURATION_MSEC,
6133 NL80211_FTM_STATS_UNKNOWN_TRIGGERS_NUM,
6134 NL80211_FTM_STATS_RESCHEDULE_REQUESTS_NUM,
6135 NL80211_FTM_STATS_OUT_OF_WINDOW_TRIGGERS_NUM,
6136 NL80211_FTM_STATS_PAD,
6137
6138 /* keep last */
6139 __NL80211_FTM_STATS_AFTER_LAST,
6140 NL80211_FTM_STATS_MAX = __NL80211_FTM_STATS_AFTER_LAST - 1
6141};
